                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15286862" author="rdblue" created="Tue, 17 May 2016 15:38:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jocoda&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jocoda&quot;&gt;Joanne Dodd&lt;/a&gt;, thanks for reporting this. It looks like the problem is happening while you&apos;re initializing a long data field, which is probably field 1 in record &quot;event&quot;. Is that record defined by your code? I&apos;m wondering if you could get around this by changing your schema so that the long fields appeared first. Otherwise, the solution is to add an alignment flag that inserts bytes in the in-memory structure, right?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15288936" author="jocoda" created="Wed, 18 May 2016 13:18:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes the problem is with the long data field (field 1 in record event).  It follows the int so is offset by 4 bytes into the buffer which is causing the crash.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am not going to be able to use the workaround of changing the schema.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Agree that the solution is to insert bytes where required so that fields are aligned correctly in the buffer as required by their type.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16251717" author="edmonds" created="Tue, 14 Nov 2017 16:54:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this bug also affects Linux on sparc64: &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=881740&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=881740&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
